cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the problem of lesion detection in medical images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel approach that involves the use of attention mechanisms and multi-scale processing, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is evaluated on a benchmark dataset, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
